    "stem": "A 17-year-old girl presents with her mother who is concerned about weight loss. The patient's BMI is 15.8 kg/m2 (significantly underweight). She refuses to eat more than 600 calories/day, says she 'feels fat,' and exercises 3 hours daily. Labs show bradycardia, hypokalemia, and low estrogen. What is the MOST likely diagnosis and the primary safety concern?",
