    "stem": "A 9-year-old boy with known sickle cell disease is brought to the clinic by his mother for sudden-onset pallor and profound fatigue over the past 3 days. There is no joint pain, fever, or respiratory distress. His hemoglobin is 4.1 g/dL (baseline 8.5 g/dL) and his reticulocyte count is 0.3% (reference range 0.5–1.5%). Which of the following best explains this presentation?",
