    "category": "Cardiovascular",
    "subcategory": "Heart Failure",
    "stem": "A 60-year-old man with heart failure and an ejection fraction of 35% is seen in clinic for a follow-up visit. He reports progressive fatigue over the past 4 weeks. His current medications include lisinopril 10 mg daily and furosemide 40 mg daily. Vital signs are stable, and lung exam reveals mild basilar crackles. He has no signs of acute decompensation. Which of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?",
